1 hair removal under the supervision of a physician as defined in
2 paragraphs 1 through 6 of subsection A of Section 725.2 of this
3 title, a certified physician assistant, or an Advanced Practice
4 Registered Nurse certified. A laser practitioner who is not a
5 physician shall complete a laser practitioner training and education
6 program. A laser training and education program may be completed
7 internally at the laser hair removal facility or via a third party,
8 provided such third-party program is overseen by a physician. A
9 laser practitioner training and education program shall include
10 forty (40) total hours of training, which may be a combination of
11 didactic training, in-person hands-on training, and performance of
12 laser hair removal procedures.
13 C. A laser hair removal facility shall be overseen by a
14 physician; provided, that Advanced Practice Registered Nurses shall
15 be exempt from this oversight requirement, as defined in paragraphs
16 1 through 6 of subsection A of Section 725.2 of this title, a
17 certified physician assistant, or an Advanced Practice Registered
18 Nurse certified.
19 D. The overseeing physician shall:
20 1. Establish proper protocols for laser hair removal provided
21 at a facility including, but not limited to, complication
22 management. A laser practitioner shall follow all written procedure
23 protocols established and revised by the overseeing physician. Such
24
