1 prot ocols shall require utilizing a physician, physician assistant,
2 or Advanced Practice Registered Nurse for complication management;
3 2. Determine the number of laser practitioners under such
4 physician's supervision; and
5 3. Review not less than ten percent (10%) of laser hair removal
6 patient records.
7 4. Every physician or physician assistant or Advanced Practice
8 Registered Nurse shall establish a relationship with patients which
9 shall include an initial evaluation, prior to treatment, that is
10 either face-to-face or via telemedicine that is performed by the
11 physician or physician assistant or Advanced Practice Registered
12 Nurse.
13 5. As part of the patient relationship, each physician or
14 certified physician assistant or Certified Advanced Practice
15 Registered Nurse shall create a patient chart. The chart shall
16 contain an informed consent, a treatment plan that includes risks,
17 benefits, alternatives, follow-up, and care for potential
18 complications.
19 E. A physician shall not be required to be physically present
20 or to supervise laser hair removal, but shall be available for
21 communication during the procedure, either in person or by two-way,
22 real time interactive communication.
